 and then a relatively recent Django version.

00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:53.800
 So let's talk about some shell commands.

00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:56.040
 So the first shell command is ls.

00:03:56.040 --> 00:03:57.760
 I showed you the man page for that,

00:03:57.760 --> 00:03:59.800
 and that lists the current files

00:03:59.800 --> 00:04:02.640
 in the current working directory.

00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:05.120
 ls -l lists them with some detail,

00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:07.840
 including the size and the last modification date

00:04:07.840 --> 00:04:09.560
 and the owner of the file,

00:04:09.560 --> 00:04:12.400
 and that little drwx stuff on the left,

00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:14.400
 well, that's the permissions,

00:04:14.400 --> 00:04:17.840
 and there is rwx, rwx, rwx,

00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:21.920
 and one is the permission that the owner would have,

00:04:21.920 --> 00:04:23.160
 fellow members of their group,

00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:25.160
 and then anyone, including anonymous users.

00:04:25.160 --> 00:04:27.560
 And so you notice that we have more permission,

00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:32.560
 we have lots more permissions than others.

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:37.720
 So the next command is pwd, pwd, print working directory.

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:42.820
 And so what happens is Unix, Linux is a multi-user system,

00:04:42.820 --> 00:04:45.200
 and our account name is dj4e,

00:04:45.200 --> 00:04:48.360
 and so /home is where all the home directories are,

00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:50.920
 and home dj4e is the home directory

00:04:50.920 --> 00:04:53.480
 for the user named dj4e.

00:04:53.480 --> 00:04:56.160
 So cd is change directory.

00:04:56.160 --> 00:04:58.880
 Now, if you type cd by itself,

00:04:58.880 --> 00:05:01.800
 you go back to your home directory.

00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:04.160
 So if I go cd space django project,

00:05:04.160 --> 00:05:05.800
 oh, and this is another thing.

00:05:05.800 --> 00:05:07.640
 There is what's called command line completion.

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:10.040
 So I know that I'm typing a directory here that exists,

00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:13.880
 djan tab underscore tab,

00:05:13.880 --> 00:05:15.840
 and then I don't have to know all the names.

00:05:15.840 --> 00:05:18.400
 You see that django projects is one of my folders,

00:05:18.400 --> 00:05:22.480
 and if it's unique, it completes it for it.

00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:25.260
 So as I'm typing, if I need to complete a file name

00:05:25.260 --> 00:05:27.440
 or a folder name, I can use the tab key.

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:31.280
 The other thing about this, that I do with pwd,

00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:34.640
 you can see now I'm in home dj4e django projects,

00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:36.120
 and it's giving me a context, right?

00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:37.280
 I'm still in my home directory,

00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:39.680
 but now I'm going down into folders

00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:42.240
 and directories and files.

00:05:42.240 --> 00:05:44.320
 Now, if I type the command cd,

00:05:44.320 --> 00:05:47.120
 it will go back to my home directory,

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:49.700
 'cause now I'm down in a subdirectory,

00:05:49.700 --> 00:05:52.920
 and I do a pwd, and you see I'm back in my home directory.

00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:56.160
 Here's another trick that I really want you to learn.

00:05:56.160 --> 00:05:59.000
 Up arrow, you can scroll, I'm up arrow, down arrow,

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.860
 up arrow, up arrow, up arrow.

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:04.440
 I can scroll up to a previous command and then hit enter,

00:06:04.440 --> 00:06:06.080
 and then run it again.

00:06:06.080 --> 00:06:08.960
 This will save you a bunch of time, okay?

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:10.760
 So I'm sitting in this folder.

00:06:10.760 --> 00:06:12.480
 So let's go back and take a look at the other things

00:06:12.480 --> 00:06:13.320
 I wanna cover.

00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:19.360
 You can use the tilde on a cd command,

00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:20.920
 and you'll see that it's showing this tilde

00:06:20.920 --> 00:06:25.800
 in the current prompt, cd tilde slash django underscore

